### Describe the bug

I want to create an endpoint that terminates requests early without executing some middlewares because it's either causing unnecessary computations or requires handling of routing in these following middlewares by calling `next(context)` based on endpoint metadata.

For this I looked into the docs and the `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Diagnostics.HealthChecks` package, specifically `HealthCheckEndpointRouteBuilderExtensions.MapHealthChecks()`. When executing, I noticed that middlewares defined after the call to `MapHealthChecks()` are also being executed.

I attached a small demo below. All requests should get a string response (`"Reached endpoint middleware"`), instead they throw a exception in the `DoNotRunMiddleware`. The same is also happening with the Healthcheck library.

### Expected Behavior

Don't call middlewares defined after a call to `MapHealthChecks()` or any other code that uses the `IEndpointRouteBuilder.CreateApplicationBuilder()` API.

### Steps To Reproduce

Execute the following ASP.NET Core file. I chose a custom middleware to make it as small as possible and to highlight it's not just a bug in `MapHealthChecks()`. All requests are caught by the endpoint.

```csharp
var app = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args).Build();

app.MapDemoEndpoint("/{**catchAll}");

app.UseMiddleware<DoNotRunMiddleware>();
app.Run();

public static class Ext
{
    public static IEndpointConventionBuilder MapDemoEndpoint(this IEndpointRouteBuilder app, string pattern)
    {
        var requestDelegate = app.CreateApplicationBuilder().UseMiddleware<DemoEndpointMiddleware>().Build();
        return app.Map(pattern, requestDelegate);
    }
}

public class DemoEndpointMiddleware
{
    public DemoEndpointMiddleware(RequestDelegate _) { }
    public async Task InvokeAsync(HttpContext ctx) => await ctx.Response.WriteAsync("Reached endpoint middleware");
}

public class DoNotRunMiddleware
{
    public DoNotRunMiddleware(RequestDelegate _) { }
    public Task InvokeAsync(HttpContext ctx) => throw new InvalidOperationException("Should not run!");
}
```

